Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). In medium bowl, mix butter, flour, and chopped nuts. Press into 9x13 inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 20 minutes. Cool completely. In a medium bowl, combine softened cream cheese and confectioners sugar, beat until smooth, then spread over cooled crust. In a large bowl, combine pudding mix with 3 cups milk. Beat until smooth, and spread over cream cheese layer. Spread whipped topping over pudding layer. Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.